    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I tried with a fresh config, and it worked for me too. Found the problem! I had to disable \"c.TerminalInteractiveShell.mouse_support\", which I had set to True.\r\nMaybe it could be useful for others to change the config from:\r\n\r\n```\r\n## Enable mouse support in the prompt\r\n```\r\n\r\nto \r\n```\r\n## Enable mouse support in the prompt\r\n## (note: prevents selecting text with the mouse)\r\n```\r\n\r\nas it's a bit counterintuitive, to me at least."
  },
